        <body>
            
            <div class="content" >
                <p style="text-align:center;font-size:15px;">
                    <strong> AGREEMENT FOR SALE</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="font-size:15px;">
                    This Agreement for Sale is made and executed on this day <apex:outputText value="{0, date, dd MMMM yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> at Bangalore.
                </p>
                <p style="font-size:15px;">
                    <strong>BY AND BETWEEN:</strong>
                </p>
                
                <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">
                    
                    <strong>Sowparnika Green Meadows Private Limited,</strong> CIN No: U68100KA2023PTC175491 a company incorporated under the provisions of the Companies Act, 2013, having its Registered office at No.750, ‘C’ Block, 1st Main Road, AECS Lay out, Kundalahalli, Bangalore - 560037. (PAN: ABLCS1614B), represented by its authorized signatory {!Booking__c.Authorized_Signato__c}. Authorized vide board resolution dated:<apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Authorized_Signatory_Resolution_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> hereinafter referred to as the <strong>“Owner and Promoter”</strong> (which expression shall unless repugnant to the context or meaning thereof be deemed to mean and include its successor-in-interest, executors, administrators and permitted assignees) <br/>
                </p>
                
                <div style="font-size:15px;padding-left:20px;">
                    AND 
                </div>

                <p style="font-size:15px;">
                    
                    <strong>{!Booking__c.First_Applicant_Name__c}</strong>, aged about &nbsp;<apex:outputText value="{0, Number,###,###,###}"> <apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Age__c}" /></apex:outputText> years, S/o/W/o/C/o. {!Booking__c.W_o_S_o_C_o__c}
                    Aadhar No. {!Booking__c.Aadhar_Number__c}, PAN No: {!Booking__c.PAN_Number__c}<br/><br/>
                    <apex:repeat value="{!Booking__c.Co_Applicants__r}" var="p">
                        <strong>{!p.Name}</strong>, aged about&nbsp;<apex:outputText value="{0, Number,###,###,###}"> <apex:param value="{!p.Age__c}" /></apex:outputText> years, S/o/W/o/C/o. {!p.W_o_S_o_C_o__c}
                        Aadhar No. {!p.Aadhar_Number__c}, PAN No: {!p.PAN_Number__c}<br/><br/>
                    </apex:repeat>
                    Residing at {!Booking__c.Address__c}, hereinafter called the <strong>“Allottee”</strong> (which expression shall unless repugnant to the context or meaning thereof be deemed to mean and include his/her heirs, executors, administrators, successors-in-interest and permitted assignees). 
                </p>
                
                <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">
                    The Promoter and Allottee shall hereinafter collectively be referred to as the <strong>“Parties”</strong> and individually as a <strong>“Party”</strong>. 
                </p>
                
                 <p>
                    <strong>WHEREAS:</strong> <br/><br/>
                </p>
                
                
                
                
                <ol style="list-style-type: upper-alpha;">
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><p>
                        The Owner/Promoter is the sole and absolute and lawful owner of residential converted lands bearing Sy. Nos: 14/2 situated at Yalachanayakanapura Village, Kasaba Hobli, Hosakote Taluk, Bangalore Rural District and Sy Nos 75/4, 75/6, 75/7 and 75/9 measuring in all 6 Acre 7½ guntas, Doddahullur Gramapanchayath Katha No.408, RDPR PID No.150300401200521125, Situated at Dodda Hullur Village, Kasaba Hobli, Hosakote Taluk, Bangalore Rural District, which is more fully described in the Schedule-A hereunder hereinafter referred to as <strong>SCHEDULE A PROPERTY.</strong>
                        </p></li>
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><p>
                        The Owner/Promoter has acquired the Schedule-A property by a sale deed dated 20-11-2024, Vide registered document No.HSK-1-14066-2024-25, in the office of the Sub- registrar Hosakote, executed by M/s. San Engineering and Locomotive Company Limited, Represented by its Managing Director Sri Ramanathan Narayanan., in the office of Sub-registrar Hosakote. 
                        
                        </p></li>
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><p>                    
                        WHEREAS, Schedule A Property is situated in an ideal locality and the Owner, also being a Promoter, is desirous of developing the same into residential apartment building, has made an application to the Hosakote Planning Authority for sanction of residential Development and accordingly, Hosakote Planning Authority instructed the Vendor to relinquish  an extent of land admeasuring 1253.97 Square Meters for Civic amenities in Schedule-A Property, and  relinquish an extent of land measuring  2503.98 Square Meters for Parks and Open spaces, 4804.40  Square Meters for Roads and Hence, the Owner/Promoter has:
                        
                        </p>
                    
                   <p>
                        a. Relinquished an extent of 1253.97 Square meters in favor of Hosakote Planning Authority under registered Relinquishment Deed dated 14.05.2025, vide registered document No.: HSK-1-02793-2025-26, in the office of the Sub-Registrar Hosakote.
                        
                        </p>
                    
                    
                   <p>
                       b. Relinquished an extent of 7308.38 Square meters in favor of Doddahullur Gramapanchayath under registered Relinquishment Deed dated 26.05.2025, vide registered document No.: HSK-1-02793-2025-26, in the office of the Sub-Registrar Hosakote.   After the relinquishment of land and after payment of prescribed fee the Member Secretary, Hosakote Planning Authority has approved the Residential Development Plan vide its approval Letter No. HPA/LAO/56/2024-25, dated 03-06-2025. 
                        </p></li>
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">  <p>
                          WHEREAS, in pursuance to the aforesaid approval of Development Plan, the Owner/Promoter has made an application to the Hosakote Planning Authority for sanction of building plan for the proposed construction of multi-storeyed residential apartment building on Schedule- ‘A’ Property and accordingly the Member Secretary, Hosakote Planning Authority has approved the building plan in favour of the Owner/Promoter vide Commencement Certificate dated:26-09-2025, bearing No. HPA/CC/286/2025-26/1737, for construction of Lower Basement, Upper Basement ground plus Nineteen   upper Floors of residential apartment building over the Schedule-‘A’ Property and named as <strong> “SOWPARNIKA  WHISPERING PETALS.”</strong>
                        </p></li>
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">  <p>
                        The Project is registered with the Karnataka Real Estate Regulatory Authority Vide RERA Certificate <strong>No: PRM/KA/RERA/1250/304/PR/301025/008211, dated:30-10-2025, issued</strong> by Karnataka Real Estate Regulatory Authority in terms of the provisions of the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016 (the <strong>“Act”</strong>) and the Rules framed thereunder by the Government of Karnataka.
                        </p></li>
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"> <p>
                        The Owner/Promoter is fully competent to enter into this Agreement and all the legal formalities with respect to the right, title and interest of the Promoter regarding the Said Land on which Project is to be constructed.
                        </p></li>
                    
                  
                   
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"> <p>
                        The Allottee has agreed to purchase the {!Booking__c.UDS__c} square feet of undivided, 
                        Share, Right, Title and interest in Schedule A property, which undivided, Share, Right, 
                        Title and interest is more particularly described in <strong>Schedule-B</strong> hereunder and hereinafter 
                        referred to as the <strong>Schedule-B Property</strong> and allotment of an Apartment   
                        in the Project vide booking form dated <apex:outputText value="{0, date, dd MMMM yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Date_of_Booking__c}" /></apex:outputText> and allottee has been allotted a 
                        Residential Apartment No {!Booking__c.Unit_NumberFor__c} having Carpet Area of {!ROUND(Booking__c.Carpet_Area__c * 0.092903, 2)} Sq. Mtrs, {!ROUND(Booking__c.Carpet_Area__c, 2)} Sq. Ft, 
                        balcony area of {!ROUND(Booking__c.Balcony_Area__c * 0.092903, 2)} Sq. Mtrs, {!ROUND(Booking__c.Balcony_Area__c, 2)} Sq. Ft, 
                       <apex:outputText rendered="{!NOT(ISBLANK(Booking__c.Plot__r.Extented_Balcony_area__c))}" 
                       value=" Extended Balcony area of {!ROUND(Booking__c.Plot__r.Extented_Balcony_area__c, 4)} Sq. Mtrs, 
                       {!ROUND(Booking__c.Plot__r.Extented_Balcony_area__c * 10.7639, 2)} Sq. Ft," />
                        <apex:outputText rendered="{!Booking__c.Plot__r.Terrace_Area__c != null}">
                        terrace area {!ROUND(Booking__c.Plot__r.Terrace_Area__c * 0.092903, 2)} Sq. Mtrs, {!ROUND(Booking__c.Plot__r.Terrace_Area__c, 2)} Sq. Ft.
                        </apex:outputText>
                        super built up area of {!ROUND(Booking__c.Built_up_area__c * 0.092903, 2)} Sq. Mtrs, {!ROUND(Booking__c.Built_up_area__c, 2)} Sq. Ft,
                        
                        and {!Booking__c.Parking__c} parking slot in which apartment unit and 
                        parking slot is more particularly described in Schedule- C hereunder and hereinafter 
                        referred to as the <strong> “Schedule C Property”</strong>. The apartment floor plan is annexed hereto 
                        and marked as Annexure-1, the payment plan is annexed hereto and marked as Schedule -2.
                        

                        </p></li>
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">  <p>
                        The Parties have gone through all the terms and conditions set out in this Agreement and understood the mutual rights and obligations detailed herein.
                        </p></li>
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">  <p>
                        The Parties hereby confirm that they are signing this Agreement with full knowledge of all the laws, rules, regulations, notifications, etc., applicable to the Project.
                        </p></li>
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"> <p>
                        The Parties, relying on the confirmations, representations and assurances of each other to faithfully abide by all the terms, conditions and stipulations contained in this Agreement and all applicable laws, are now willing to enter into this Agreement on the terms and conditions appearing hereinafter.
                        </p></li>
                    
                    <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">    <p>
                        In accordance with the terms and conditions set out in this Agreement and as mutually agreed upon by and between the Parties, the Promoter hereby agrees to sell and the Allottee hereby agrees to purchase the Apartment and parking space.
                        </p></li>
                    
                </ol>
                
                
                
                <div style="page-break-after:always;"></div>
                <div style="font-size: 14px;text-align: justify;line-height: 1.5;margin: 12px 0;">
                    <strong>NOW IT IS HEREBY AGREED BY AND BETWEEN THE PARTIES AS FOLLOWS: </strong>
                </div>
                
                <div class="sub-heading">
                    <strong>1) DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION: </strong><br/><br/>
                </div>
                <p >
                    <strong>1.1) Definitions:</strong><br/>
                    Unless the context otherwise requires, the following capitalized terms shall have the meaning set forth below.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">
                    
                    <strong>a) “Act”</strong> means the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016 (Central Act of 2016) and includes the Karnataka Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Rules, 2017 where the context so requires and all the Rules made pursuant to the Act.
                </p>
                
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>b) “Agreement”</strong> shall mean this agreement to sell the Schedule `B’ Property and construction of the Apartment, including the schedules and annexures hereto, as may be amended from time to time.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>i. “Apartment Owners/Owners”</strong> shall mean any owner or owners of Apartments in the Project.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>ii. “Applicable Law”</strong> means all laws, statutes, regulations, codes, bye- laws, ordinances, treaties, judgments, decrees, directives, rules, guidelines, orders, policies and other requirements of any Governmental Authority having jurisdiction over the Schedule “A” Property which are in effect or as may be amended, modified, enacted or revoked from time- to-time hereafter.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>iii. “Approvals”</strong> shall mean license and plan sanctioned by the Hosakote Planning Authority for construction of the Project i.e., Work Order bearing No. HPA/CC/286/2025-26/1737, dated: 26/09/2025.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>iv. “Association or Association of Apartment Owners or Owners Association”</strong> shall all mean the same, being the Association of Apartment Owners to be formed by the Seller/Promoter, in respect of the Project as per the provisions of the Karnataka Apartment Ownership Act, 1972, in the form of a Company or Trust or Society or in the form of any other entity.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>v. “Association Agreement”</strong> shall mean the Maintenance Agreement between the Association and the service provider for maintenance of the Common Areas, Amenities and Facilities in the Project.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>vi. “Appropriate Government”</strong> means the State Government of Karnataka.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>vii. “Balance Sale Consideration”</strong> shall mean any part of the sale consideration/cost of construction and other charges which has not been paid and is required to be paid under this Agreement in terms of the instalments set out in terms of Annexure-2 hereto.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;" ><strong>viii. “Carpet Area”</strong> means the net usable floor area of an Apartment, excluding the area covered by the external walls, areas under services shafts, exclusive balcony or veranda area and exclusive open terrace area, but includes the area covered by the internal partition walls of the Apartment.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>ix. “Completion Certificate”</strong> shall mean the certificate of completion for the building/s issued by the Project Architect, certifying that the same having been built as per the Specifications annexed hereto and in accordance with the sanctioned plans and its fitness for occupation.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>x. “Completion Period”</strong> shall mean on or before by or such extended time as provided in Clauses herein, before which the Promotor would have applied for and secured the Occupancy Certificate for all or any of the Tower/s in the Project.</p>
                    
                
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xi. “Common Areas of the Project”</strong> shall mean and include areas demarcated and declared as the common areas of Project, which are used in common by all the owners/occupants on payment of Common Area Maintenance Charges and does not include the reserved common areas. The Common Areas in the Project are subject to such reasonable, non-discriminatory rules and regulations as are prescribed by the Seller/Promoter/promotor or Owners Association to be followed by all the owners/occupiers of the apartments in the Project.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xii. “Common Amenities &amp; Facilities of the Project”</strong> shall mean and include those amenities and facilities of the Project, the Common Amenities and Facilities of the Project are subject to such reasonable, non-discriminatory rules and regulations as are prescribed by the Seller/Promoter or the Association to be followed by all the owners/occupiers of the Apartments and does not include reserved facilities.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xiii. “Deed of Declaration”</strong> shall mean the deed of declaration to be executed by the Seller/Promoter/promotor to submit the Project, the Common Areas, the Common Amenities and Facilities of the Project under the provision of the Karnataka Apartment Ownership Act, 1972.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xiv. “Force Majeure”</strong> shall mean the occurrence of one or more of the following events:</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">1. War, flood, drought, fire, cyclone, earthquake or any other calamity caused by nature including those detailed in the clause relating to events of Force Majeure.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">2. Epidemic, Pandemic, Sars, Ebola, Swine Flu, Covid-19 (Corona Virus) and any other flu or virus outbreaks within more general terms such as “disease” or “illness” that may cause measures to address or contain an outbreak and also such other disease or illness that may be listed or covered under general terms such as “government action”, “government order”, “government circulars”, “national emergency’ or “quarantine”, lock down due to the spread of any disease which may or may not require social/physical distancing and isolation measures to restrict the spread of the disease referred to above.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">3. any other calamity caused by nature affecting the regular development of the Project.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">4. reasons beyond the control of the Seller/Promoter/Promoter.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xv. “Interest”</strong> means the rate of interest payable by the Seller/Promoter or the Purchaser/s, as the case may be in terms of this Agreement which is to be calculated at prevailing interest rate of State Bank of India highest Marginal Cost of Lending Rate (MCLR) plus 2%.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xvi. “Land”</strong> shall mean and include land in Schedule `A’ Property.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xvii. "Local Authority”</strong> or “Authority" shall mean any union, state, local or other governmental, administrative, regulatory, judicial or quasi-judicial authority or self-regulating authority or agency, commission, board, tribunal, court, Bangalore Development Authority, Bangalore Electricity Supply Company Ltd., Real Estate Regulatory Authority, Real Estate Appellate Tribunal and shall include any other competent authority under the Act and having jurisdiction over the Schedule “A” Property.</p>
                    
                <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xviii. “Limited Common Area”</strong> shall mean the Purchaser/s Car/Scooter Parking Area, terrace area and such other areas, which are allotted for the exclusive use by the apartment owners in Project as they would be attached to such Apartments and capable of being used by the owners of the apartments and to be maintained by the owners of such apartments at their cost and not as part of the Common Area.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xix. “Occupancy Certificate”</strong> means the Occupancy Certificate or such other certificate by whatever name called, issued by the LPA/local body.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xx. “Other Costs Charges and Expenses”</strong> shall mean all the amounts set out in Annexure-2 hereto, which amounts the Purchaser/s is/are required to pay in addition to the Sale Consideration, Cost of Construction and Statutory Payments as per Annexure-2.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxi. “Party”</strong> unless repugnant to the context, shall mean a signatory to this Agreement and <b>“Parties”</b> unless repugnant to the context, shall mean a collective reference to all the signatories to this Agreement.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxii. "Person"</strong> shall mean any natural person, limited or unlimited liability company, corporation, general partnership, limited liability partnership, proprietorship, trust, union, association, court, tribunal, agency, government, ministry, department, commission, self-regulatory organization, arbitrator, board, or other entity, enterprise, authority, or business organisation and shall include any other person as defined under the Act.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxiii. “Plan”</strong> or “Sanctioned Plan” shall mean the building plan, which is approved by the Local Authority prior to start of the Project.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxiv. “Project”</strong> shall mean and include the proposed development of Apartments in the subject Property envisaged under the scheme of development.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>(a) “Purchaser/s Car/Scooter Park/s”</strong> shall mean the Car/Scooter parking space/s allotted to the Purchaser/s for his/her/their exclusive use so long as the Purchaser/s own/s and occupy/ies the Schedule “C” Apartment or by any of the occupiers of the Schedule “C” Apartment under the authority or agreement with the Purchaser/s herein.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxv. “Possession”</strong> shall include “Deemed Possession” agreed to be delivered on receipt of Occupancy Certificate or before expiry of notice of completion, whichever is earlier.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxvi. “Rules”</strong> means the Karnataka Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Rules, 2017.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxvii. “Regulations”</strong> means the Regulations made under the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxviii. “Section”</strong> means a section of the Act.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxix. “Sale Deed”</strong>  shall mean the deed of sale to be executed by the Seller/Promoter/Promotor, for legally conveying the absolute right, title and interest in the Schedule `B’ Property &amp; Schedule `C’ Property Apartment on the terms and conditions contained therein under the Scheme.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxx. “Specifications”</strong> shall mean specifications of the Project set out in Annexure-3 attached hereto, based on which the Project and the Residential Apartment Buildings shall be constructed/completed.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxxi. “Statutory Payments”</strong> shall mean statutory charges including Goods and Service Tax (“GST”) and Cess as applicable from time to time, which will be payable by the Purchaser/s in addition to the Sale Consideration, Cost of Construction and Other Cost Charges and Expenses, under this Agreement.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxxii. “Super Built-Up Area”</strong> of any Apartment shall mean the aggregate of (i) the Carpet Area of an Apartment and (ii) thickness of the external walls balconies and terraces and proportionate share in the Common Areas and such of the Common Areas used for housing the Common Amenities and Facilities in the Project.</p>
                    
                    <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"><strong>xxxiii. “TDR/Permissible FAR”</strong> shall mean the Transferable Development Rights and Floor Area Ratio as defined in Karnataka Town and Country Planning Act, 1961. </p>
                    <p style="font-size:15px;">
                        <strong>c) AGREEMENT TO SELL AND CONSTRUCT: </strong>
                        
                    </p>
                        <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">
                            That in pursuance of the aforesaid agreement and in consideration of the Purchaser/s agreeing to participate in the scheme of development and paying the consideration stipulated for sale of undivided share and the cost of construction of Apartment and all applicable taxes, charges, etc., agreed to be paid in terms of this agreement and subject to the Purchaser/s complying with all the terms herein, the Seller/Promoter hereby agree to sell and the Purchaser/s hereby agree to purchase the Property herein consisting of an Undivided Share of Land, right, title, interest and ownership in the land in Schedule `A’ Property and described in Schedule `B’ herein and further the Seller/Promoter hereby agree to construct for the Purchaser/s the Apartment in terms of the scheme envisaged as above and on prompt payment of the amounts stipulated above and convey the same. The total sale price includes the booking amount paid by the Purchaser/s to the Seller/Promoter. 
                        </p>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    <p style="font-size:15px;">
                        <strong>d) CONSIDERATION FOR SALE OF SCHEDULE `B’ &amp; `c’ PROPERTY AND APPLICABLE TAXES AND OTHER CHARGES: </strong>
                        
                    </p>
                
                     <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                         <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"> 
                             <p>
                                 The Seller/Promoter has agreed to sell, and the buyer/Purchaser/s has agreed to purchase Schedule `B’&amp;C Property herein for a total sale consideration of <strong>Rs. {!totlbasicPriceinIndian} (Rupees {!TotalBasicAmountInWords} only)</strong>. The Total Price of Apartment includes recovery of price of land, construction of not only the Apartment but also the Common Areas, internal development charges, external development charges, cost of providing electrical connectivity, electric wiring to the apartment, lift, water line and plumbing, finishing with paint, tiles, doors, windows, fire detection and firefighting equipment in the common areas, and includes cost for providing all other facilities, amenities and specifications to be provided within the Apartment and the Project in terms of Specifications. Provided that in case there is any change / modification in the taxes, the subsequent amount payable by the Purchaser/s to the Seller/Promoter shall be increased based on such change / modification. The Total Price above excludes Goods and Service Tax (GST) and Cess in connection with the construction of the Project, by whatever name called and the same shall be payable by the Purchaser/s to the Seller/Promoter/ from time to time.
                             </p>
                         </li>
                       <li style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;"> <p>
